        {
          "insert": "The object-shape block of the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "block vocabulary"
        },
        {
          "insert": ", and the state carrier of its documentation doctrine: a state-shape shows what a structure's state looks like — a recursive field tree of name, type, optionality, and meaning — beside a linked JSON example instance of that shape. An "
        },
        {
          "insert": "interaction-surface",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/40-block-vocabulary/60-interaction-surface"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " lists the operations on that state; "
        },
        {
          "insert": "code",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/40-block-vocabulary/20-code-block"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " blocks carry annotated source evidence."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
